Item 1.01 Entry into a Material Definitive Agreement
     Atmel Sarl (the "") and Atmel Switzerland Sarl (""), each a wholly-owned subsidiary of Atmel Corporation (the ""), along with the Company, entered into a Facility Agreement, dated as of March 15, 2006, among the Borrower, as the borrower, Atmel Switzerland, as a guarantor, the Company, as a guarantor, the financial institutions listed therein, as original lenders (the ""), and Bank of America, N.A., as facility agent and security agent (the ""). The closing of the Facility Agreement occurred on March 15, 2006. The Facility Agreement has a term of five years from the date of the Facility Agreement and permits the Borrower to borrow on a revolving basis up to the lesser of US$165 million or 85% of its eligible receivables less certain reserve amounts. No amounts are currently borrowed under the Facility Agreement.
Borrower
Atmel Switzerland
Company
Lenders
Facility Agreement
     Under the Facility Agreement, the Borrower may borrow at an interest rate of LIBOR plus 2% per annum ("") or at the reference rate initially set by the facility agent (""). Maturity periods for LIBOR Loans may be one, two or three months. The maturity period for Reference Rate Loans is one month.
LIBOR Loans
Reference Rate Loans
     Interest on the loans is payable monthly in arrears with respect to Reference Rate Loans and at the end of an interest period in the case of LIBOR Loans. Principal, together with accrued and unpaid interest, is due at maturity.
     The obligations of the Borrower, Atmel Switzerland and the Company under the Facility Agreement are secured by:
     The Facility Agreement requires the Company to comply with a fixed charge coverage ratio and maintain minimum available cash of not less than $100 million. The events of default under the Facility Agreement include payment defaults, breaches of covenants, misrepresentations, cross defaults and cross acceleration with certain other indebtedness, bankruptcy events and changes of control. The terms of the Facility Agreement also subject the Company to certain other covenants.
     
