Executive Officer Actions; Letter Agreement
On October 17, 2008, Dr. Bernard Pruniaux notified Atmel Corporation ("Atmel") that he was giving three months notice of his decision to retire from his employment as Atmel's Vice President and General Manager, ASIC Business Unit. Pursuant to a letter agreement between Dr. Pruniaux and Atmel, to ensure a smooth transition of responsibilities, Dr. Pruniaux will remain as Vice President, Managing Director of Atmel Rousset SAS during the three month notice period, ending January 17, 2009, and will work on assignments and projects as specified in the letter agreement. Following January 17, 2009, it is anticipated that Dr. Pruniaux would work as a consultant for up to twelve months and would be compensated on a daily rate based on his current annual gross salary.
Also on October 17, 2008, the Board of Directors of Atmel named Jean Vaylet as Vice President and General Manager, ASIC Business Unit. Mr. Vaylet has been a Vice President of Atmel since 2000, and has previously managed the biometrics business unit and the previously divested Grenoble imaging business unit.
 
     Pursuant to the requirements of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, the registrant has duly caused this report to be signed on its behalf by the undersigned hereunto duly authorized.


