Item 1.01. Entry Into a Material Definitive Agreement.
On March 4, 2010, Atmel Rousset S.A.S. (""), a wholly-owned subsidiary of Atmel Corporation ("") incorporated under the laws of France, entered into a Stock Purchase Agreement (the "") with LFoundry GmbH, incorporated under the laws of Germany (""), providing for the sale of Atmel's 200mm silicon wafer fabrication business located in Rousset, France to LFoundry through a sale and transfer of the stock of a French company ("") having all the assets and liabilities related to the wafer fabrication business (the "").
Atmel SAS
Atmel
Stock Purchase Agreement
LFoundry
Fabco
Sale
Under the terms of the Stock Purchase Agreement, Atmel SAS will receive nominal cash consideration in the Sale, subject to potential post-closing adjustments based on the assets and liabilities of Fabco at the time of closing. The closing of the Sale is anticipated to occur during the second quarter of 2010, and is subject to certain customary closing conditions for a transaction of this nature. The Stock Purchase Agreement contains representations, warranties and covenants customary for a transaction of this nature, and further provides that Atmel SAS shall indemnify LFoundry, and LFoundry shall indemnify Atmel SAS, against certain losses up to a cap of 500 thousand Euros, subject to certain exceptions.
In connection with the closing of the Stock Purchase Agreement, Atmel SAS and Fabco will enter into certain other ancillary agreements, including a Manufacturing Services Agreement (the ""), pursuant to which Atmel SAS will purchase wafers from LFoundry for a minimum of three (3) years following the closing on a "take-or-pay" basis.
Manufacturing Services Agreement
Atmel expects to record certain costs and fees upon closing, and anticipates a loss on this sale, which could be material, the amount of which cannot currently be determined as it is dependant on the final terms and conditions of certain ancillary agreements, including the Manufacturing Services Agreement.
 
