Stockholder Approval
 
25. .  The Plan shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of the State of California (except its provisions).
Governing Law
choice-of-law
 
26. .  If any provision of the Plan is or becomes or is deemed to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable for any reason in any jurisdiction or as to any Participant, such invalidity, illegality or unenforceability shall not affect the remaining parts of the Plan, and the Plan shall be construed and enforced as to such jurisdiction or Participant as if the invalid, illegal or unenforceable provision had not been included.
