Departure of Named Executive Officer; Appointment of Executive Officer.
 
On March 24, 2011, Rod Erin, Vice President, RFA, Non-Volatile Memory and Aerospace business of Atmel Corporation (the "Company") announced his intention to retire from the Company in mid-2011 and his resignation as an executive officer of the Company, effective immediately.  Mr. Erin expects to remain a non-executive employee of the Company until his retirement.
 
Robert Valiton, Vice President of Sales for Americas, EMEA and Global Sales Operations of the Company, has been promoted, effective March 24, 2011, to the position of Senior Vice President, General Manager and will assume responsibility for the RFA, Non-Volatile Memory and Aerospace business previously overseen by Mr. Erin.
