Item 5.07.         Submission of Matters to a Vote of Security Holders.
 
On May 20, 2011, Atmel Corporation (the "") filed a Current Report on Form 8-K under this Item 5.07 to report the results of its Annual Meeting of Stockholders (the "") held on May 18, 2011.  The Company is filing this amendment to that Form 8-K to disclose the Company's decision, in light of the vote at the Annual Meeting, regarding the frequency of presenting a stockholder advisory vote on executive compensation to its stockholders.
Company
Annual Meeting
 
At the Annual Meeting, the Company's stockholders voted to hold an advisory "say-on-pay" vote every year.  In  light of that vote, the Company's Board of Directors determined, at its August 12, 2011 meeting, to hold annual advisory "say-on-pay" votes on executive compensation, unless and until the Board of Directors determines to modify that decision in the future.
